1.00	Turkish_Foundation_for_Combating_Soil_Erosion	Turkish Foundation for Combating Soil Erosion	The Turkish Foundation for Combating Soil Erosion (Turkish: ), better known in abbreviated form as TEMA, is a non-governmental organization for reforestation and the protection of natural habitats in Turkey. It was founded on September 11, 1992 by Turkish businessmen Hayrettin Karaca, who has an UN Environment Award, and Nihat Gökyiğit. TEMA is the leading (NGO) in Turkey with 236,000 voluntary members.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/38/Location_map_Istanbul.png/250px-Location_map_Istanbul.png
